    "client_msg_id": "F278CC2B-9CC6-41A6-8129-C8E0BC098477",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "One interesting idea when it comes to streaming app content comes up if the platform was more like an OS and app developers were forced to submit apps through an app store. Since bad app code/performance would cost more to the hoster of the system, they would be incentivised to think about performance. In turn, they would force developers to think about performance as well and put measures in place that would encourage updates to apps be _faster on the same hardware (as it would save them money)._ That's the complete opposite of say today's Apple for example :)\n\nImagine a sustainable tech company that provide products that become faster every year!\n\nThis works only if the platform has control over the content though, which is not the case for Mighty. I'm fully on the game dev side in this fight :p",
    "user": "UUY4LQJN4",
    "ts": "1620054457.189300",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
